Let’s be honest – who here doesn’t love sushi? I could eat it daily although I don’t need or want that much rice every week. Which is why this low-carb, 100% plant-based rainbow cucumber sushi is the perfect compromise! I’ve shared options similar in my story for years but this is awesome! By @alphafoodie

This rainbow cucumber sushi is not only 100% plant-based , but can be made in under 15 minutes and perfect for a healthy, delicious low-carb lunch or snack served alongside a delicious vegan avocado dip!

🤤 Who’s in a fry mood?! 
 
🍟 The French Fry Recipe I Eat Everyday!
By @theflexibledietinglifestyle 
 
✅ Macros for the WHOLE Batch:
302 Cals, 63g Carbs, 3g Fat, 7g Protein

✳️ Ingredients:
350g Russet Potato
Sea Salt
Non Stick Butter Spray (added 3g Fat to the Macros for the sprays)

❇️ Directions:
1️⃣ Take your russet potato and cut into what style fries you want. I cut mine into these wedge hybrids just because it’s easier. I use my crinkle cutter to do so as well. They are like $5 on amazon so it’s a great purchase in my opinion. Add them to a bowl of cold water for about 15 minutes. 
 
2️⃣ After 15 minutes, drain the water and then spray the fires with non stick butter spray and toss in sea salt. Add to air fryer on 400 degrees F for 15 minutes. Keep in mind you’ll need to flip them after 8 minutes. Then it’s time to enjoy! That simple! 
 
#fries #frenchfries #potatoes

Gluten-free, dairy-free, artificial sugar-free peanut butter banana muffins - does it get better?! 🙌🥜🍌 
 
➡️ Swipe to see both videos and pictures 😋 by @feelgoodfoodie 
 
📝 INGREDIENTS 
3 ripe bananas
⅔ cup unsalted peanut butter
3 tablespoons honey
2 large eggs
1 teaspoon vanilla
1 ¼ cup oat flour
1 ½ teaspoon baking powder
1 teaspoon baking soda
¼ teaspoon salt
½ teaspoon cinnamon
¼ teaspoon nutmeg
 
👩‍🍳 Instructions
1. Preheat the oven to 375°F. Line a standard muffin pan with muffin papers. 
2. In a large bowl, beat the bananas with a hand mixer until well mashed.
3. Add the peanut butter and honey. Beat until smooth. Add the eggs and vanilla. Beat on low until just combined. 
4. Combine the oat flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and spices in a small bowl or large measuring cup. Stir to distribute. 
5. Transfer the dry ingredients to the wet and stir with a spatula until just combined. Do not over mix. Some small lumps are ok. 
6. Scoop the batter into the prepared muffin pan, filling the cups just below the top. Add sliced bananas, if using. 
7. Bake for 15-17 minutes, until a cake tester inserted in one of the center muffins comes out with just a couple crumbs. Allow to cool in the pan for 10 minutes before serving. 
 
#bananas #banana #oatflour #oats #healthydesserts #muffins #muffin #healthymuffins #baking #healthybaking #healthyrecipes #healthyrecipe

Follow 👉 @default_thinking to learn WHY you're overeating and HOW to STOP the overeating, binge eating, stress eating and lose weight in a healthy and sustainable way. 
 
Absolutely delicious and packed with so much flavor, especially for such a quick and easy meal 🙌🏼 
 
Sweet and Smoky Drumsticks 🍗
By @spiced.nice
 
Find the written recipe below, enjoy! #spicednice ⬇️⬇️⁣
⁣
🍗6 drumsticks ⁣
🍗1/4 cup honey ⁣
🍗2 tsp paprika ⁣
🍗2 tsp smoked paprika ⁣
🍗2 tbsp Cajun seasoning ⁣
🍗2 tsp chili powder ⁣
🍗2 tsp garlic powder ⁣
🍗1 tsp black pepper⁣
🍗1 tsp salt or to taste⁣
🍗3.5 tbsp avocado  oil ⁣
 ⁣
1. Mix all the ingredients in a bowl except for the chicken. Once you have a red paste, add in the drumsticks and score the chicken all over so the marinade flavors the chicken to the bone. If you have time, I recommend marinating for at least 30 minutes. ⁣ 
 
2. Spray the air fryer with nonstick cooking spray then place the drumsticks inside. Air fry at 380°F for 8 mins then flip and cook for another 12-15 minutes (flip every 5 mins). Depending on the size of your drumsticks and the air fryer being used (I’ve noticed different air fryers cook slightly differently) keep an eye on the drumsticks towards the end and cook until the internal temperature has reached 165°F. ⁣ 
 
3. Alternative BAKING INSTRUCTIONS: preheat oven to 400°F and bake for 35-40 mins or until internal temperature has reached 165°F. Flip once halfway through and enjoy! 
 
#grilling #chicken #grill

Follow 👉  @drewthomasfitness 
He has gone from chubby to fit and has laid out the process so you can do it too! 
 
Who’s down for this? 
 
🫐 BLUEBERRY BAKED OATS 🫐 
By @dcfoodporn 

Ingredients:
-1 cup oats
-1/2 banana
-1/2 cup frozen blueberries
-1 tbsp honey
-1 tsp baking powder
-pinch of salt
-1/4 cup dairy free milk

Steps:
-blend ingredients together
-add to an oven safe container
-air fry at 350F for 10 minutes (or bake in the oven for ~20)
-enjoy!
-tag me if you try it 😋

#blueberry #blueberries #bakedoats #oats #oatmeal #easybreakfast #easyrecipe #foodandwine #foodnetwork #foodbeast #thrillist #athome #homecook #easyrecipes #snackrecipe

Follow @bodysmartfitness for the best fitness tips 
 
Egg White Breakfast Cups (Under 50 Calories) 🍳 
By: @buzzfeedtasty 
-
Ingredients
(for 6 servings)
2 cups spinach, 14 calories (60 g)
1 roma tomato, 11 calories
2 cups egg white, 250 calories (480 mL)
salt, to taste, 0 calories
½ teaspoon pepper, 0 calories
-
Preparation
Preheat the oven to 350˚F (180˚C).
Lightly grease a muffin tin.
Then divide equally the spinach across 6 cups.
Dice the tomato, then fill the cups with the tomato and egg whites.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake for 15 minutes, or until the whites have set.
Serve hot.
Enjoy! 
 
#eggs #egg #eggwhite #eggwhites #protein #mealprep #foodprep

Follow @bodysmartfitness for the best fitness tips! 
 
What’s better than feeling good after a few healthy meals 😉😁 

1,2,3,4 or 5? Which one is your favorite?👇👇👇👇...By @sailor_bailey 
.....
1️⃣dEATS: soft boiled pasture-raised eggs + loads of sautéed broccoli 👋 folicacid + avocado slices + crispy mushrooms and some ETBTB seasoning ✨
